IC1 - an Icelandic male voice
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Notation
Pre-aspiration is marked with an 'h'
	frakki = _ f r a h J- I _
Post-aspiration isn't marked in the same way:
	b, d, g, J- are unaspirated, p, t, k, c are aspirated.
Unvoicing of nasals and liquids is marked by adding a 0 (zero). 
	n (nýta, _ n i: t a _) vs n0 (hnýta, _ n0 i: t a _).
Consonant length is not marked, only length of vowels. Note the difference between "kyssa" and "kisa" below. The qualitative difference between long and short vowels was nowhere near as great as anticipated, so in many cases they may be interchangable.

